    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Currently, I'm just re-exporting the `Configure` component and including the `SearchOptions` type directly, which side-steps the issue without having to use `@ts-ignore` or type assertions.\r\n\r\n```tsx\r\nimport { SearchOptions } from \"@algolia/client-search\";\r\nimport {\r\n  Configure as ConfigureAlgolia,\r\n  ConfigureProps,\r\n} from \"react-instantsearch-hooks-web\";\r\n\r\nexport const Configure = (props: ConfigureProps & SearchOptions) => (\r\n  <ConfigureAlgolia {...props} />\r\n);\r\n```",
    "created_at": "2023-06-08T03:41:10Z",
